# Implementation Plan - AI Social Engineering Defense System (SEDS)

This plan outlines the step-by-step development of SEDS, following the survival-first priority order requested.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This plan assumes a clean environment. We will be using FastAPI for the backend and React (Vite) for the frontend as per the TRD.
> Groq API key and Supabase credentials will be required for full functionality.

## Proposed Changes

### Phase 1: Survival Core (Backend & AI)
Goal: Get the core image-to-AI pipeline working.

#### [NEW] [backend/main.py](file:///e:/MUDASSIR/BTECH/HACKATHON/VHACK2026/backend/main.py)
- Initialize FastAPI app.
- Set up basic error handling and CORS.

#### [NEW] [backend/routes/analyze.py](file:///e:/MUDASSIR/BTECH/HACKATHON/VHACK2026/backend/routes/analyze.py)
- Implement `/analyze-image` endpoint.
- Integrate `EasyOCR` for text extraction.
- Integrate `Groq` for scam analysis using the provided prompt template.

#### [NEW] [backend/services/ocr_service.py](file:///e:/MUDASSIR/BTECH/HACKATHON/VHACK2026/backend/services/ocr_service.py)
- Wrapper for EasyOCR.

#### [NEW] [backend/services/groq_service.py](file:///e:/MUDASSIR/BTECH/HACKATHON/VHACK2026/backend/services/groq_service.py)
- Wrapper for Groq API calls.

---

### Phase 2: Risk Assessment
Goal: Implement the 10-question risk questionnaire and AI-enhanced result.

#### [NEW] [backend/routes/risk.py](file:///e:/MUDASSIR/BTECH/HACKATHON/VHACK2026/backend/routes/risk.py)
- Implement `/risk-score` endpoint.
- Logic for rule-based scoring (unsafe answer = +10).
- Integrate Groq for risk prediction and recommendations.

---

### Phase 3: Frontend & Authentication
Goal: Build the user interface and secure it with Supabase.

#### [NEW] [frontend/](file:///e:/MUDASSIR/BTECH/HACKATHON/VHACK2026/frontend/)
- Initialize Vite-React project.
- Implement Login, Dashboard, Analyzer, and Risk Assessment pages.
- Integrate Supabase Auth.

#### [MODIFY] [backend/main.py](file:///e:/MUDASSIR/BTECH/HACKATHON/VHACK2026/backend/main.py)
- Add JWT middleware to protect endpoints using Supabase.

---

### Phase 4: Security Hardening & Demo Stability
Goal: Implement requirements from [RATELIMIT.md](file:///e:/MUDASSIR/BTECH/HACKATHON/VHACK2026/RATELIMIT.md) and finalize demo readiness.

#### [MODIFY] [backend/main.py](file:///e:/MUDASSIR/BTECH/HACKATHON/VHACK2026/backend/main.py)
- Implement rate limiting (IP + user-based).
- Add strict Pydantic models for input validation.

#### [NEW] [backend/services/fallback_service.py](file:///e:/MUDASSIR/BTECH/HACKATHON/VHACK2026/backend/services/fallback_service.py)
- Heuristic fallback logic for scam detection if AI/OCR fails.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- `pytest`: Run unit tests for backend logic (scoring, validation).
- `curl/Postman`: Test `/analyze-image` with sample screenshots.

### Manual Verification
1. **Survival Test**: Upload a known scam screenshot and verify JSON output from backend.
2. **Risk Test**: Complete the questionnaire and verify score calculation.
3. **Security Test**: Attempt to spam the API to trigger rate limiting.
4. **UI Test**: Verify the responsive design and loading states.
